1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Hey, Brian. You got a sec?

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Yeah, I know what you're gonna say. It's all right.

3
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,000
No, I heard you got in trouble. I feel awful.

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:12,000
It's fine. It was my first slip-up in nine years of micing you.

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Well, thanks for being a good friend.

6
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Sure. Anytime. How about you and Jim? Everything squared away?

7
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Yeah. Mostly.

8
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Pam, phone call.

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Um, I'm sorry.

10
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Um, hey, say hi to Alyssa.

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Will do.

12
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Okay. Thank you.

13
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Sure.

14
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Hey, boom guy.

15
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Oh, hey, Meredith.

16
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,000
When are you gonna boom me?

17
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Uh, listen, they're cracking down on us talking to the subjects.

18
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:46,000
It's a lame rule, but you know, I wanna... I'll see you later.

19
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,000
Got it.

20
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Okay.

21
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Hey. So I hear you're bringing in some people to interview for the sales job?

22
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,000
That's right. Couple old friends.

23
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Ballers only must be this cool to ride.

24
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Well, uh, see, you raised it.

25
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Did I? Oh, yes, I did.

26
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Wallace is letting me hire a junior sales associate to sit at Jim's desk while he's away in Philly.

27
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Finally, I'll have someone at my desk clump who gets me.

28
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:45,000
It's like, really, Jim?

29
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:48,000
You don't understand the difference between a slaughterhouse and a rendering plant?

30
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Uh, remind me not to lend you any dead cows or horses.

31
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Wow.

32
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,000
You know what, man? I deserve this job.

33
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,000
I scored Stone and Sun suit warehouse with you,

34
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,000
and God knows to get the Scranton White pages with Jan.

35
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,000
I went above and beyond.

36
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,000
And under.

37
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:06,000
You know what?

38
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,000
You're gonna get your interview, okay?

39
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,000
I know that you're going head to head against some real superstars,

40
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,000
but you've got a really good chance.

41
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Clark has no chance.

42
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,000
I mean, he's up against my buddy Roll for God's sake.

43
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Guy goes fishing with hand grenades.

44
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:20,000
And Trevor?

45
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,000
He'll make you laugh so hard you'll puke your pants.

46
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,000
This sucks.

47
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,000
You know, you put in 12 grueling weeks at a company, and what do they do?

48
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:29,000
They make you compete for a promotion, like an animal.

49
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:32,000
You know, I thought this was an office, not the Thunderdome.

50
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Big changes coming to the old desk clump.

51
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:38,000
No longer a Pam-Jim alliance against Dwight.

52
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Now it is Dwight and a friend Axis against Pam.

53
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,000
You could have just called that an alliance too, right?

54
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,000
I chose my words very carefully.

55
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Things are a little delicate with me and Pam right now.

56
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:54,000
And if my working in Philly is gonna end up doubling the Dwight in her life,

57
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,000
that's only gonna make things worse.

58
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Whew.

59
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,000
You interviewing for the sales job too?

60
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
No. You're interviewing for it.

61
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,000
I'm getting it.

62
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Well, I wouldn't be so sure about that.

63
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,000
I mean, I've been working here 12 weeks.

64
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,000
That's a full season of Homeland.

65
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,000
A ton of things can happen in that amount of time, as we've seen.

66
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,000
I'm Rolf. Rolf-all.

67
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Rolf-all.

68
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,000
Sounds kind of like Rol-dol.

69
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Go to hell.

70
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,000
There he is.

71
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Hey.

72
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,000
Come on, buddy.

73
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,000
Let's do this.

74
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,000
Sorry, Rolf goes first. You don't compare.

75
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:34,000
When you're with the R-O-L-F, you're literally rolling on the laughing floor.

76
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,000
Come on.

77
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Nice.

78
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Rolf is my best friend, and he is the man.

79
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Cool, calm, and collected 24-7.

80
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Just try and rattle Rolf, I dare you.

81
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Such a sweet guy.

82
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,000
When are you talking to David Wallace?

83
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:52,000
I'm talking to him this afternoon, but don't get your hopes up.
